DIGEST
SB 56 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Connick
Present law provides for the jurisdictional organization of the Lafitte Area Independent
Levee District. Proposed law retains present law and changes the name of the levee district
from the Lafitte Area Independent Levee District to the Lafitte Area Levee District.
Present law provides for governance and appointments of the commissioners of the Lafitte
Area Independent Levee District including Senate confirmation of commissioners and
requirements for commissioners. Proposed law provides the Lafitte Area Levee District will
be governed by the board of commissioners of the Southeast Louisiana Flood Protection
Authority-West Bank and for four members to be appointed from a list of six nominations
submitted by the legislative delegation representing the portion of Jefferson Parish the levee
district is located in.
Present law provides for the composition of the board of commissioners of the Southeast La.
Flood Protection Authority-West Bank. Proposed law provides for changes to the number
of members of the authority from seven to nine, with one residing within the territorial
jurisdiction of the Lafitte Area Levee District.
